content: See #86592. No one was automatically assigned but rust-highfive. I presume this is due to the recent T-libs/T-libs-api split.

Hmm, I don't think it's related, the team list is maintained by hand (i.e. doesn't depend on the GitHub team API AFAIK): https://github.com/rust-lang/highfive/blob/abe01ef16d6d442342f254e30cd9c9afd8d3ac3e/highfive/configs/rust-lang/rust.json#L15-L22
That's odd. I assumed libs was renamed libs-api, leaving the new libs with nothing.
T-libs-impl became T-libs. But does highfive not assign based on labels anyway and looks at files modified instead?

The 8472 said:

T-libs-impl became T-libs. But doesn't highfive assign based on labels anyway and looks at files modified instead?

correct
